data.enText: a relationship between two organizations or different departments in an organization, involving the exchange of information or ideas

data.chText: 我们的作用是确保学校与家长间的联系。
data.enText: Our role is to ensure liaison between schools and parents.
We work in close liaison with the police.
a person whose job is to make sure there is a good relationship between two groups or organizations

data.chText: 白宫与工人组织的联络人
data.enText: the White House liaison to organized labor

data.chText: （尤指一方或双方已婚的）私通，通奸
data.enText: a secret sexual relationship, especially if one or both partners are married

means: (尤指一方或双方已婚的)私通，通奸

tr: a channel for communication between groups
example: he provided a liaison with the guerrillas

tr: a usually secretive or illicit sexual relationship

value.def: Liaison is co-operation and the exchange of information between different organizations or between different sections of an organization.

example.ex: Liaison between police forces and the art world is vital to combat art crime.
example.tran: 警方和艺术界的联手对于打击艺术品犯罪至关重要。

example.ex: ...those who work in close liaison with alcoholics.
example.tran: 在工作中与酗酒者密切接触的人们

value.def: If someone acts as liaison with a particular group, or between two or more groups, their job is to encourage co-operation and the exchange of information.

example.ex: I have a professor on my staff here as liaison with our higher education institutions...
example.tran: 我的员工中有一名教授充当我们和高等教育机构的联络人。

example.ex: She acts as a liaison between patients and staff.
example.tran: 她在病人与医护人员间充当沟通的桥梁。

value.def: You can refer to a sexual or romantic relationship between two people as a liaison .

example.ex: She embarked on a series of sexual liaisons with society figures.
example.tran: 她开始接二连三地与社会名流有染。
